## 5. ServerModelDataPointer

The `ServerModel` is a **second root pointer** that lives alongside `DataModel`. It owns server-side services and the network Handle. Think of it as the "server-only" layer.

```cpp
// ServerModel.hpp
#pragma once
#include <memory>

class ServerStorage;
class ServerScriptService;
class NetworkHandle;

class ServerModel {
public:
    static ServerModel* Get();
    void Init();

    std::shared_ptr<ServerStorage>      serverStorage;
    std::shared_ptr<ServerScriptService> serverScriptService;
    std::shared_ptr<NetworkHandle>      handle;

private:
    static ServerModel* s_instance;
    ServerModel() = default;
};
```

